
================================================
NOTEWORTHY SYSTEMS
================================================

- search autocomplete 
- search engine 
- web crawler 
- video streaming service 
- mp3 streaming service 
- image sharing service 
- chat / messaging systems 
- file storage and sahring systems 
- recommendation systems (users recommended content based on history, interests, etc.)


================================================
KEY CONCEPTS
================================================

- horizontal vs. vertical scaling 
- load balancing
    - know common algorithms
        - round-robin
        - least connections
        - weighted round-robin 
    - get familiar with load balancing technology (reread the book on load balancing)
- distributed systems fundamentals 
    - fault tolerance
    - concurrency control
    - data consistency 
 - network protocols 
    - TCP/IP
    - HTTP/HTTPS
    - streaming protocols for mp3 or mp4 (DASH, etc.)
- database fundamentals
    - know the different types of databases and when to use them
        - SQL
            - structured DATA
            - ACID properties
            - suitable for transactions
            - know some specific technologies (MySQL, PostgreSQL)
        - noSQL (various types)
            - flexible xchemas
            - horizontal scalability
            - suited for large datasets and varying data structures
            - know some specific technologies
                - mongoDB (document store)
                - redix (key-value)
                - cassandra (wide-column)
                - Neo4J (graph)
        - in memory
        - understand indexing (accelerating query execution for specific data)
        - understand blob storage (efficiently store large amounts of unstructured data)
        - understand search-optimized databases (designed for fast and efficient search of large datasets using special indexing techniques)
- know various caching strategies
    - cache-aside
    - write-through
    - refresh-ahead
- know various cache eviction policies
    - LRU
    - LFU
- replication 
    - speak to its availibility / fault tolerance benefits 
    - speak to synchronous vs. asynchronous replication and its impact on consistency vs. availability
- understand messaging systems
    - discuss event driven architecture, and how asynchronous communication improves scalability / robustness
    - understand the technologies used
        - kafka
        - rabbitMQ

- understand web app architecture
    - microservices vs. monolithic architecture and the tradeoffs of each 
    - API gateways 
        - centralized entry point for client requests
        - routing to different services
        - rate limiting 
        - handles security 
    - CDNs (content delivery networks)
    - proxies
        - understand their role in network architecture and security 
        - know the difference between a forward and reverse proxy 
    - API design 
        - graphQL
        - REST
        - understand concepts of clean API design 

